title: For Sale:  Beretta 92FS Brigadier
postcontent:
Up for sale is a rare Beretta 92FS Brigadier This Beretta is in great condition. It is the hard to find Brigadier version of the 92FS.  It features the matte black finish, heavier profile slide, dovetail front and rear 3 dot sights, DA/SA trigger and ambgi safety/decock lever.  It wears the CTC Crimson Trace Laser Grips, CTC Model LG 302 grips ($189.00 Value) and includes 2 factory 15 round mag.  I can leave the grips on for an additional $100 or install factory grips for the current asking price.
Like the standard 92FS, the 92FS Brigadier is a double/single-action semiauto pistol that employs an open-slide, short-recoil delayed locking-block system, which yields a faster cycle time and delivers exceptional accuracy and reliability. In particular, the open-slide design practically eliminates “stove-piping” and helps flawless cycling and feeding even after thousands and thousands of rounds. Add to this the extra weight of the Brigadier slide, and you get enhanced durability even above these specifications. To minimize recoil, the slide features a heavy profile--which also enhances durability--and the grips are Hogue soft rubber wraparound panels that greatly absorb the momentum of the pistol upon firing. Other important features of the 92FS Brigadier include the dovetailed front and rear sights that can be easily replaced by the user, as well as a maximum magazine capacity of 15 rounds (9mm Parabellum) for top-notch firepower. Add to this the legendary benefits of the Beretta 92FS (M9), and you get a variant equally suited for home defense, competition, duty or concealed carry and more.
This gun will be sold on a first email contact. First come, first serve. Serious buyers only.No trades
